b'' b'' b'we need terrain data for a visualization research currently taking place' b'in tel-aviv university. we have two databases that we are currently working' b'on, but we would like to work on more databases, possibly more complicated' b'and ones that will give prettier images.' b'' b'before i describe what kind of data we need, let me mention that we are' b'going to present a paper titled "photo-realistic imaging of digital terrains"' b"which describes the research and the results, in the eurographics'93" b'conference in barcelona, this september. we are going to show a video-tape' b'with some of our results, so any good data that we will receive will be' b'presented in the tape, with a mention of the donator.' b'' b'we are working on databases consisting of aerial or satelite photographs,' b'and terrain elevation maps (dtm).' b'each database consists of a 2d array of height values (any data format can' b'be used for each value), and a corresponding 2d array of color values (can' b'be gray-level, 256-color value or full 24-bit r/g/b values. other format can' b'also be used). we work on 512x512 and 1024x1024 resolution databases.' b'' b'if anybody has access to this kind of data, or knows where we can get such' b'data files, please respond in this news group, or better email us' b'directly b'' b'' b'of course, the names of the people who will help us get the data will be' b'cited in our paper, and in further publications.' 